profile:
Executive Touch Painters Toronto is a full service painting and renovating company providing service to residents of Toronto and the rest of GTA.  We specialize in exterior and interior painting of both residential and commercial projects. No job is too big or small for us. We provide a complete range of painting services, and with well over a decade of experience in the industry, ET Painters Toronto has been focusing at providing exceptional service to its clients while maintaining the highest level of integrity. 


At Executive Touch, we don't stop there. We provide full service home renovation services including drywall repair and installation, caulking, stucco work, as well as general contracting work. Our stellar reputation of high quality service and fast and efficient work has helped us to grow our business phenomenally.


Please feel free to phone one of our service representatives who can provide advice and guide you in your renovation project. Our foremen answer our phones and with years of experience behind their back, it ensures you get the right advice and consultation right over the phone. 


We service Toronto, Vaughan, Richmond Hill, Newmarket, Mississauga, Brampton, Milton, Aurora, Etobicoke, Scarborough and the rest of the GTA. Phone us today to transform your property into a marvel!


Why would you choose to use Executive Touch Painters Toronto for your next project:
• We provide Guarantee on all our work 
• Provide full workers compensation 
• 5 million liability insurance 
• Fully bonded workers 
• 30 years of experience in the painting industry
• Hundreds of satisfied clients to provide reference of work 
• Use of top quality paint including Benjamin Moore, Dulux, Behr, Sherwin Williams, Para etc. 
• We are exceptionally clean and tidy and utilize drop sheers for every job.


Home Renovations - remodeling living rooms, living space, corridors, ceilings, flooring. 


Bathrooms - remodeling or building from scratch - experience in tiling, grouting, painting, priming, tile installation (marble, ceramic, laminate), plumbing, bathtub and toilet installation 


Kitchens - remodeling or installation of new kitchen - we do everything from tiling, standard and custom made cupboard installation, backsplash, painting, countertop (laminate or granite) installation, plumbing, etc. 


Painting - priming, painting, puttying, sanding - walls, ceilings (interior only)

profile:
Mississauga/Oakville/Milton, Burlington/Hamilton, Toronto

ABOUT US

****

Natik Painting was founded by a team of professionals in 1978. We have grown our team to a base of competent employees including highly-trained painters and artists. In addition to standard painting for residential and commercial projects, we do murals of all scales and faux-finishing like ragging and smooshing in wide-ranging styles. Our interior design specialists have employee degrees in fine arts to make your place look its best! For large projects, we guarantee the excellence that we established throughout our many years of experience.

NATIK PAINTING ADVANTAGE

****

Experience: We have excelled in thousands of interior and exterior painting projects for over more than 30 years.
Courtesy: Fast and friendly service with no shortcuts. We also provide color consultation, interior decorating, and design services. Natik Painting offers free estimates. 
Craftsmanship: Our artists and painters are veteran artists with degrees in fine arts.
Quality: Natik Painting uses top-quality Benjamin Moore paint and only professional equipment.
Mastery: We have mastered a wide variety of faux-finishing and painting techniques such as ragging, smooshing, stripes, etc. We customize the technique highly to suit your space.

OUR MISSION STATEMENT
Established in 1978, we ensure the highest quality painting service and materials at the most competitive price. 
We provide solid preparation beforehand. We believe it is key to a proper job. 
We take the risks out of painting. We make the effort to eliminate any probability of damage or spills to your floors, furniture, and we use low-VOC paints.
We try to get the courtesy details right. We do the job quickly, allow flexibility for color changes between coats, and upon completion of the job, all remaining paint will be given to the customer. This is to ensure that touch-up paint will be available to you in the event of any future accidents.

COMPETITIVE EDGE
In terms of our superior professional quality in combination with our reasonable pricing, we believe there is no other painting company in the GTA that provides a similar offering.
Feel free to contact us by e-mail or by telephone!

SAMPLE OF PREVIOUS COMMERCIAL CLIENTS
Samsung Electronics Canada Ltd.
Labatt Brewing Company Ltd.
Casa Abruzzo Benevolent - Villa Charities Inc.
And MOST of all -thousands of homeowners.
We hope to hear from you soon!

profile:
Trying to remodel a bathroom by yourself? Forget the hassle and let the Bathroom Builders team efficiently install your bathroom to eliminate your stress.
The process starts with a fun and informative in-home consultation with your personal Bathroom Builders design consultant. We provide this service free of charge, so you have nothing to lose and everything to learn! Your design consultant will simplify the sometimes complex home renovation process by walking you through product selection and design.
When it’s time to start constructing your new bathroom, factory-trained Bathroom Builders installers will complete your project in as little as a few days, answering any questions along the way. Our professional installers will respect your family’s home. They’ll be on time, courteous and, most importantly, they’ll get the job done right the first time.
Bathroom Builders install both our own line of products and products from the best national brands. With countless colors, textures and styles to choose from, if you can dream it, we can likely make it happen. Learn more about our bathroom remodeling products: Explore our replacement bathtubs, walk-in bathtubs, bathtub to shower conversions, bathroom vanities, bathroom flooring and more.
Bathroom Builders are fully licensed and insured. Bathroom builders brand products carry a manufacturer's limited lifetime warranty against product defects. Financing is available. We proudly serve in all of the Greater Toronto Area including Mississauga, Oakville, Burlington, Hamilton, Toronto, Richmond Hill, and Vaughan

profile:
Who We Are

We are an award winning residential and commercial painting company that services Hamilton, Burlington, Oakville and surrounding areas. We were founded by a couple of women who believe strongly in equal rights and abilities of men and women in the trades. Our company hires and trains both men and women who possess the qualities that it takes to be a part of this amazing team. 

What Makes Us Stand Above The Rest?

The satisfaction of our customers is our number one priority. Without customers we wouldn't have a business. In order to provide the best quality service and workmanship to our clientele, we invest in training and education for all of our painters.

Each of our painters are certified in Workplace Health and Safety, WHMIS, Working at Heights, Handling of Dangerous Goods, Understanding Paints and Coatings as well as educated in class with training videos and hands on job training. 

All of our painters are hired employees who are properly insured and covered with WSIB.

My name is Painter Pete Codsi and I have been a household option for over 20 years as an independant painter, not a sub-contractor. I provide honest and sensible methods to get your home back to the integrity it once was - fresh and happy - quickly, and I'm very tidy. I provide my painting services in local areas close to Hamilton from Caledonia to Flamboro, Grimsby, Stoney Creek, Dundas and Burlington.
 
Painter Pete utilizes funky ladders that make climbing cathedral walls childs-play and carries enough drop-sheets to cover a gymnasium floor. He posseses a design sense that would be expected from an experienced painter of 25 years.
 
Most of the paint Pete uses is latex while converting whenever it becomes practical - good-bye rotary phones and hello micro-technology. All brush-work is done without tape as Pete does not splatter. Pete's hand-drawn lines are supremely fast and verging on artistic genius.
name: Painter Pete Codsi
